{"created":"2015-06-03T18:16:59+00:00","modified":"2015-06-03T18:34:19+00:00","valid":{"from":"2015-06-03T18:34:19+00:00","to":"3015-06-03T18:34:19+00:00"},"hreflang":"en","title":"Forming A Community Of Conservation In San Diego","published":"2015-06-03T18:34:00+00:00","teaser":"Building on a model from the U.K., a group in San Diego is helping to build a more conservation-minded, sustainable lifestyle.","itags":["npr_api","411769272"],"guid":"af31d52a-6427-47df-af32-1fe028b8d4d9","contentencoded":"<p>Building on a model from a <a href=\"http://www.transitionstreets.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">U.K. organization</a>, a group of people in San Diego has come together to help each other build a more conservation-minded, sustainable lifestyle.</p><p>It&#8217;s a response to the drought, of course, but <a href=\"http://www.transitionsd.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Transition Streets San Diego</a> is also focused on energy, transportation, food and waste.</p><p><a href=\"http://hereandnow.wbur.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Here & Now</em></a>&#8216;s Robin Young talks with <strong>Jamie and Leslie Edmonds</strong>, the couple leading the effort, and group member <strong>Gawain Tomlinson</strong>.</p><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.kpbs.org/news/2015/may/04/mid-city-alternative-water-police/\" target=\"_blank\">Read more about Transition Streets SD</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SIkKWD2W8rg\">[Youtube]</a></p><h4>Guest</h4><ul><li><strong>Jamie Edmonds</strong>, co-founder of Transition Streets San Diego.</li><li><strong>Leslie Edmonds</strong>, co-founder of Transition Streets San Diego.</li><li><strong>Gawain Tomlinson</strong>, member of Transition Streets San Diego.</li></ul>  <div class=\"fullattribution\">Copyright 2015 NPR. To see more, visit <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/\">http://www.npr.org/</a>.<img src=\"http://www.google-analytics.com/__utm.gif?utmac=UA-5828686-4&utmdt=Forming+A+Community+Of+Conservation+In+San+Diego&utme=8(APIKey)9(MDAyOTcwND